  "body": "- [ ] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nAn item of valid solidity syntax (an omitted component in a destructuring assignment - see example foo function below) isn't recognised in solidity tests (even though it's compiled fine when it's in the contracts directory).\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. run truffle init in empty directory to create starting project\r\n2. edit the example solidity test contract in test/TestMetacoin.sol to add the following function that uses a destructing assignment with an omitted component (see e.g. http://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/latest/control-structures.html#destructuring-assignments-and-returning-multiple-values ):\r\n\r\n```\r\n\tfunction foo(uint x, uint y, uint z) returns (uint) {\r\n\t\tvar (,q,) = (x, y, z);\r\n\t\treturn q;\r\n\t}\r\n```\r\n\r\n3. run truffle test\r\n \r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nI expected the tests to compile and run, since the function is valid solidity.\r\n\r\nIt's interesting that if I add the same foo function not to the tests, but to the code being tested (e.g. to contracts/Metacoin.sol), that it works fine - truffle can compile it. I think perhaps there's some other javascript (not solc) that parses the test contracts that doesn't like this - I notice it mentions PEG in the output?\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\ntruffle test throws an error along the lines of:\r\n\r\n```\r\nSyntaxError: Expected identifier but \",\" found. Line: 26, Column: 8\r\n    at peg$buildStructuredError (PATH_REDACTED\\npm\\node_modules\\truffle\\build\\cli.bundled.js:184440:12)\r\n    at Object.peg$parse [as parse] (PATH_REDACTED\\npm\\node_modules\\truffle\\build\\cli.bundled.js:197026:11)\r\n    at Object.parse (PATH_REDACTED\\npm\\node_modules\\truffle\\build\\cli.bundled.js:76082:23)\r\n    at PATH_REDACTED\\npm\\node_modules\\truffle\\build\\cli.bundled.js:218574:32\r\n    at tryToString (fs.js:456:3)\r\n    at FSReqWrap.readFileAfterClose [as oncomplete] (fs.js:443:12)\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Windows 10 under git bash shell / MINGW64\r\n* Truffle version: v3.2.7\r\n* Ethereum client: TestRPC\r\n* node version: v6.10.3\r\n* npm version:  3.10.10\r\n",
